        <p>
            <span style="font-size: 18px"><span style="color: #ff8c00">How to Start?</span></span></p>
        
        <p> Installing InstaSign plugin is as easy as configuring page layouts. Just drag &amp; drop the &ldquo;Capture Signature&ldquo; publisher action on page layout of the object you which to capture the signature.</p>
        <p> Once added in publisher layout you can see this action in Salesforce1 Screen as show in screenshots above. </p>
              
        <p>
            <span style="font-size: 14px;border-bottom: 1px solid #ff8c00;"><span style="color: #ff8c00">For adding the publisher action to Salesforce1</span></span></p>
        
        <p>
            Let&rsquo;s take an example of adding a button on standard object Account (same process can be followed to add button on any custom objects too).
        </p>
        <ol style="line-height:25px">
            <li>
                Go To Setup <apex:image value="{!URLFOR($Resource.InstaSign, 'InstaSignImages/RightArrow.png')}" width="30" height="10" style="padding-left:7px;padding-right:7px;"/> Account<apex:image value="{!URLFOR($Resource.InstaSign, 'InstaSignImages/RightArrow.png')}" width="30" height="10" style="padding-left:7px;padding-right:7px;"/> Page Layouts</li>
            <li>
                Click &ldquo;Edit&ldquo; on Desired page layout</li>
            <li>
                Click Actions
            </li>
            <li>
                Drag &ldquo;Capture Signature&ldquo; action into the &ldquo;Publisher actions&ldquo; section
            </li>
            <li>
                Finally click Save.
            </li>
        </ol>           
           <p>
            Now you can see the new publisher action &ldquo;Capture Signature&ldquo; in Salesforce1 screen in clicking the menu options on the Account object detail page of Salesforce1 as shown in the screenshots</p> 
